## Row "The GambiConf"

row-what-is-gambiconf--title = The GambiConf

row-what-is-gambiconf--body-paragraph-1 = At GambiConf, we celebrate the genuine hacker spirit.

row-what-is-gambiconf--body-paragraph-2 =
  Here, the stage belongs to out-of-the-box talks. In past editions, for example, we learned about
  <a data-l10n-name="link-water">building a computer out of water</a>,
  <a data-l10n-name="link-satellite">reverse engineering a satellite's communication</a>,
  <a data-l10n-name="link-flappy-bird">writing a Flappy Bird in Assembly</a> and
  <a data-l10n-name="link-lcd">playing music with an LCD monitor and a radio!</a>

row-what-is-gambiconf--body-paragraph-3 =
  This is a multilingual conference, not tied to any single technology. We focus on the purpose behind
  the projects presented, the unique nature of each session, and what we can learn from something
  different and, perhaps, unusual!

row-what-is-gambiconf--body-paragraph-4 =
  If you have something to share (especially if it's weird!), GambiConf is your place.
  And if you'd rather get inspired by ideas you wouldn't find anywhere else, don't miss the next edition!

row-what-is-gambiconf--body-paragraph-5 =
  You can learn more about what GambiConf is in this short opening video from the last edition:

